    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I am looking for a way to define multiple public member variables of an extension class at the same time. I need to main python compatibility. Does this syntax work?\r\n\r\n    @cython.cclass\r\n    class Store:\r\n        cython.declare(id=cython.int, num_employees=cython.int, visibility=\"public\")",
    "closed_at": "2017-09-02T06:55:51Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "OWNER",
            "body": "No, there is no way to declare multiple names with one `declare()` call.\r\nNote that this is a support question more than a bug. As such, it is best suited for the cython-users mailing list.\r\nIf it's meant as a feature request, that's fine for the issue tracker, but it's unclear from your description why this feature is needed. Why can't you write more than one line?",
